# Test Changes

## Context
Keep test changes reliable, readable, and aligned with existing project conventions.

## Rules for adding/updating tests:

- Keep tests co-located with the feature and follow existing naming conventions
- Ensure new failure cases include clear assertions for expected behavior
- NEVER introduce non-deterministic tests (timers/network) without a stable deterministic strategy
- DO NOT add or update snapshots/fixtures without confirming the changes are intentional
- AVOID duplicating setup logic; reuse shared helpers where available

## How to verify
- Review test changes for determinism, naming, and co-location
- Confirm snapshot/fixture diffs are intentional
- Run the relevant test suite(s) for the changed area
- Run `yarn test:typecheck` to catch type errors introduced by test changes
- Run `yarn test:update` only when snapshot/fixture updates are intended and valid for this repo
- All verification commands must be valid for this project and align with existing scripts
